.TH "RTCPEERCONNECTION.GETIDENTITYASSERTION" "3JS" "June 26, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
RTCPeerConnection.getIdentityAssertion \- RTCPeerConnection:
getIdentityAssertion() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]getIdentityAssertion()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]RTCPeerConnection\f[R] interface initiates the gathering of an
identity assertion.
This has an effect only if the \f[CR]signalingState\f[R] is not
\f[CR]\(dqclosed\(dq\f[R].
.PP
It is not expected for the application dealing with the
\f[CR]RTCPeerConnection\f[R]: this is automatically done; an explicit
call only allows to anticipate the need.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
getIdentityAssertion()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
A \f[CR]Promise\f[R] which resolves to an identity assertion encoded as
a string.
.SH EXAMPLE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] pc = \f[B]new\f[R] RTCPeerConnection();

pc.setIdentityProvider(\(dqdeveloper.mozilla.org\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] assertion = \f[B]await\f[R] pc.getIdentityAssertion();
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
WebRTC
